<p>In the latest development, the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) captured El-Fasher, the main city in North Darfur, after an extended siege that ended on Monday, October 27, 2025 . Since entering the city, multiple reports describe mass executions, sexual violence, abductions and house-to-house raids, and residents have fled in large numbers as aid operations are disrupted . International agencies and observers have demanded independent investigations and raised alarms about possible ethnic-based crimes, while humanitarian access and medical care in the city are reported to be severely compromised .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/lejEb-c9zrkrUtWPGrchlC6SS3BbqqENkH-Oz8pT5lBaH-7Am-y5UTYwegaeL75yNzLD5PVWvkMo5zlGkQz8j33W0h7dNyFMSGYgwXcXi-gYS_eMR09SyArR4bvGz4VH3Xxdj943FO-0xuc' alt='Reporting image from coverage of Sudan&#x27;s civil war and the RSF assault on El-Fasher' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Satellite evidence: Analysts, including Yale&#x27;s Humanitarian Research Lab, say satellite imagery shows clusters and discoloration consistent with human bodies and blood in parts of El-Fasher, strengthening forensic concerns</li><li>Health sector hit: The World Health Organization publicly condemned reports that more than 460 patients and their companions were killed and that six health workers were abducted at the city&#x27;s Saudi Maternity Hospital</li><li>Civilian death toll: The Sudan Doctors Network reported roughly 1,500 civilians executed while fleeing El-Fasher over the week surrounding the city&#x27;s fall, calling the pattern ethnically targeted killings</li><li>Aid workers targeted: Humanitarian groups and reporters say aid staff have been attacked or killed and that operations face severe constraints after reported killings of volunteers and abductions in the region</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Survivors interviewed by The Washington Post: Survivors described families shot down and people held for ransom as they fled Darfur&#x27;s killing fields. (<a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/11/01/sudan-darfur-el-fashir-rsf-genocide/'>Washington Post</a>)</li><li>Sudan Doctors Network: The scale and scope of violence in El-Fasher represents a true ethnic-based genocide and follows a scorched-earth policy, the group said. (<a href='https://theweek.com/world-news/sudan-darfur-rsf-rapid-support-africa'>The Week</a>)</li><li>World Health Organization (WHO): WHO condemned the reported killing of patients and the abduction of health workers at El-Fasher&#x27;s Saudi Maternity Hospital. (<a href='https://theweek.com/world-news/sudan-darfur-rsf-rapid-support-africa'>The Week</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/the-take-2/2025/10/31/what-does-the-fall-of-el-fasher-mean-for-sudan'>What does the fall of el-Fasher mean for Sudan?</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/11/01/sudan-darfur-el-fashir-rsf-genocide/'>Families shot down, held at ransom as they flee Darfur’s killing fields</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/sudans-brutal-civil-war-escalates-as-paramilitary-forces-go-on-killing-rampage'>Sudan’s brutal civil war escalates as paramilitary forces go on killing rampage</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/sudan-is-being-ravaged-by-a-civil-war-the-world-has-overlooked'>Sudan is being ravaged by a civil war the world has overlooked</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://theweek.com/world-news/sudan-darfur-rsf-rapid-support-africa'>Sudan stands on the brink of another national schism</a> - theweek.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/africa/20251031-sudan-photos-videos-el-fasher-massacres-rsf'>Sudan: What photos and videos can tell us about the El-Fasher massacres</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/un-demands-probe-into-horrific-accounts-of-executions-gang-rapes-abductions-in-sudan/'>UN demands probe int